id: pm-7x0wqg
title: Full coverage gate flakes when real all-package install exceeds generic 30-second unit timeout under load
description: "The extension acceptance that installs all 15 bundled packages is a real filesystem-heavy integration path. It completes in about 10 seconds alone but reaches 28-30 seconds while 354 coverage files run concurrently, causing cleanup cascades and nondeterministic release-gate failures. Give this single broad acceptance an explicit bounded budget without weakening assertions or global timeouts."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[3]: "area:packages","area:testing","quality:flake"
created_at: "2026-07-24T07:01:04.342Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-24T07:19:53.281Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-24T07:19:26.623Z"
author: claude-code-agent
parent: pm-wo8
resolution: Assigned the real all-package acceptance a test-local 45-second budget while retaining its full install assertions and the suite-wide 30-second default.
expected_result: The real 15-package wildcard/all acceptance remains deterministic during parallel full coverage without weakening global timeout policy.
actual_result: "Owner suite and complete 6,212-test exact coverage pass; the acceptance completed under load without cleanup cascades."
